OL,3,C'Leave Portsmouth alone': Council's
OL,4,Cmessage to government
OL,6,FCllr Pitt said there 'is considerable
OL,7,Fanger and genuine concern' across
OL,8,FPortsmouth after the authority was
OL,9,F'compelled' to submit proposals on how
OL,10,Fit could reorganise and merge with
OL,11,Fother councils, to create new unitary
OL,12,Fauthorities.
OL,14,FHe also highlighted that Portsmouth
OL,15,F'is not a failing local authority' and
OL,16,Fhas been a resounding success since it
OL,17,Fwas created in 1997, and unlike other
OL,18,Fcouncils, is financially sound.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/8
