OL,3,C'Leave Portsmouth alone': Council's
OL,4,Cmessage to government
OL,6,F"Currently Portsmouth is in a better
OL,7,Fposition financially than many other
OL,8,Fcouncils, and we have significant
OL,9,Fconcerns about what new councils would
OL,10,Finherit, given the eye-watering
OL,11,Fdeficits experienced by other local
OL,12,Fauthorities, notably Hampshire County
OL,13,FCouncil with its #136m forecast
OL,14,Fdeficit for 2026-27.
OL,16,F"I understand the Government's desire
OL,17,Fto have unitary councils, but
OL,18,FPortsmouth is already a sustainable
OL,19,Funitary so should be left alone."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/8
